cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about the expressive power of first-order logic and monadic second-order logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses graph invariants and their impact on the expressive power of logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of logic on different classes of graphs. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper uses mathematical concepts such as tree depth and Feferman-Vaught theorem. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graph structures and their properties.
